> Have you ever been awoken by the smell of pimiento dulce infused cod while taking a siesta on the Spanish coast? Me neither! But it sounds delightful and our chef André had that very experience when he was on holiday last year. Let his smokey cod with roasted new potatoes, chorizo dressing and caramelised courgettes whisk you away to the shores of Spain this dinner time!

Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Cut the @New Potatoes{1}(halved lengthways) and place in a #roasting tray{}. Toss in @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Pop in the oven for ~{25%mins}.

Peel the @Red Onion{1}, remove the ends, cut in half and slice into thin half moon slices. After ~{15%mins} add the sliced onion to the potatoes in the oven, toss together and roast for a further ~{10%mins}.

Whilst the potatoes are cooking, marinate the @Cod Fillets{2}. Zest the @Lemon{1} and mix with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and the @Smoked Paprika{1}. Smear this all over the cod and place the fish back in the fridge while you get on with everything else.

Chop the ends off the @Courgette{1}, cut into six strips lengthways and then cut the strips into 3cm batons.

== Dressing ==

Peel and finely chop the @Garlic Clove{2}(finely chopped). Pick and roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{5%leaves}(roughly chopped). Juice half the lemon. Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on a medium heat. Add the @Diced Chorizo{1} and cook for ~{5%mins} until the chorizo is nicely browned. Remove from the heat and stir in the chopped garlic. Add the lemon juice and chopped parsley. Stir well and transfer to a #bowl{}.

== Roasted Potatoes and Cod ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, remove from the oven and cover with foil to keep warm. Heat your #grill{} to its highest setting and cook the cod for ~{7-8%mins} or until the centre is opaque.

== Caramelised Courgettes ==

Whilst the fish is cooking, heat a large frying pan until very hot. Add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to the pan and add the courgettes. Allow the courgettes to take on a nice golden brown colour before turning them. This should take around ~{1%minute}. Continue this process until the courgettes are golden brown all over. Season with a good pinch of @salt{} and a generous grind of @black pepper{}.

Juice the other half of the lemon and squeeze over the fish. Serve on a bed of roasted potatoes, red onions and courgette. Finish the dish with the chorizo vinaigrette. Delicious!